ProcessTask.name: Change End Date
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Updates the process form validTo field when the value of the user's End Date changes on the user profile.

ProcessTask.name: Change Last Name
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Copies last name from user profile to the process form. Invoked when last name on user profile changes. See Lookup 'USR_PROCESS_TRIGGERS' for how this task is triggered when the user profile changes.

ProcessTask.name: Change First Name
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Modifies the 'name givenName field' on the process form when the First Name field changes on the user profile

ProcessTask.name: Change Participant
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Updates the value of the participant attribute on the process form when the value of the user's department changes on the user profile.

ProcessTask.name: Change Division
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Updates the process form with the new value of the Division when the value changes on the user profile

ProcessTask.name: Change Department
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Updates the value of the department attribute on the process form when the value of the user's department changes on the user profile.

ProcessTask.name: Change Email
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Updates the Email field on the process form when the value of the user email changes

ProcessTask.name: Change Telephone Number
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Modifies the value of the telephone number field on the process form when the value of the 'Telephone Number' changes on the user profile

ProcessTask.name: userName Updated
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: invokes eFBS SCIM REST endpoint with replace op with new value of userName field whenever it changes

ProcessTask.name: name givenName Updated
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: invokes eFBS SCIM REST endpoint to update with new value of naem givenName field whenever it changes

ProcessTask.name: Email Updated
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Triggered whenever the Email attribute on the process form changes. There should only be one value for email but this is stored as a child table entry to satisfy the SCIM specification, so this task must manage the removal or previous value where appropriate and adding of the new value to the child table

ProcessTask.name: Telephone Number Updated
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Triggered whenever the Telephone Number attribute on the process form changes. There should only be one value for Telephone Number but this is stored as a child table entry to satisfy the SCIM specification, so this task must manage the removal or previous value where appropriate and adding of the new value to the child table

ProcessTask.name: organization Updated
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: invokes eFBS SCIM endpoint to update the organization attribute for the user

ProcessTask.name: division Updated
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Invokes the eFBS SCIM endpoint to update the division for the user when the value of the division on the user profile changes

ProcessTask.name: department Updated
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Invokes eFBS SCIm service endpoint to update the user's department when the value of the department on the process form changes

ProcessTask.name: validFrom Updated
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: invokes eFBS SCIM service with request to update the user validFrom value when the value on the process form changes

ProcessTask.name: validTo Updated
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: invokes eFBS SCIM service with request to update the user validTo value when the value on the process form changes

TaskResponse.name: Certify
TaskResponse.RSC_DESC: Attested that the entitlement is correct

TaskResponse.name: Reject
TaskResponse.RSC_DESC: Attested that the entitlement is not correct

TaskResponse.name: Certify
TaskResponse.RSC_DESC: Attest that the entitlement is correct

TaskResponse.name: Reject
TaskResponse.RSC_DESC: Attest that the entitlement is not correct

ProcessTask.name: Delete Account
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: eFBS SCIM service does not support delete/revoke . May be implemented as a PATCH request toset the validTo date field but semantics TBC so NOOP for now. Allow multiple because NOOP.

ProcessTask.name: Enable Account
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Enables account by setting status to active i.e. active == 1. Also sends PATCH REST call to eFBS server with active='true'

ProcessTask.name: Disable Account
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Disables the account setting active=1.. Sends PATCH REST call to eFBS server with active='false'

ProcessTask.name: Change Start Date
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: Updates the process form validFrom field when the value of the user's Start Date changes on the user profile.

ProcessTask.name: Admin Updated
ProcessTask.MIL_DESCRIPTION: invokes eFBS SCIM endpoint to update the admin attribute for the user.
